antigravity-plugin-cc (limeflash fork)
======================================

This project is a fork of:

  simplybychris/antigravity-plugin-cc
  https://github.com/simplybychris/antigravity-plugin-cc
  Licensed under the MIT License.

The fork extends the upstream plugin with the goal of reaching feature
parity with openai/codex-plugin-cc — adding background job control
(/agy:status, /agy:result, /agy:cancel), branch-base code review,
adversarial review, and an optional stop-gate review hook — while
preserving the upstream's security-conscious defaults (no auto-approve,
no global write-dir expansion).

Roadmap inspiration is drawn from:

  openai/codex-plugin-cc
  https://github.com/openai/codex-plugin-cc
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Architecture concepts re-implemented from codex-plugin-cc (job control,
state persistence, render layer) are attributed in the source comments
where applicable. No source code is copied directly from codex-plugin-cc
in this initial fork commit; future PRs that port specific files will
include the upstream attribution header and Apache 2.0 NOTICE as
required.

All modifications relative to the simplybychris baseline are documented
in CHANGELOG.md from version 0.5.0 onwards.
